		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64731454">Society used to recognize that child development requires special restrictions to correctly work. This is why we have age limitation on alcohol consumption, because after hundreds of years of no such limitations we clearly understood negative consequences in the adulthood.<br> <br>Digital communications, and social media in particular, are extremely toxic to normal development. It amplifies neuroticism, it encourages narcissism, and it does enable unprecedented levels of digital bullying. The solution must not be a half-measure and 'do something' bromides - the solution should be<b>outright ban on all social media</b> for anyone under legal age. This does not mean you must be prevented from accessing it, but it does mean that you must be prevented from being targetable/reachable (e.g., having account) on it.</div>
	</div>

