		<div id="comment_body_64731534">There have always been bullies, and there will always be. Young bullies grow up to be adult bullies. <p>
There are even crybullies, who bully from a weakness perspective. </p><p>
As far as I know, this will not ever stop. It is part of humanity, and usually stems from insecurity or in less common situations, pathological personas. </p><p>

We have to define bullying - there is an entire spectrum of definitions, starting with simple disagreement, and microparsing of everyone's words and interaction.It's hard to get anything<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64731534">

</div>
